<subSubSection id="FA9AB2FAFFB06652C6A5E43633D1FCF9" pageId="7" pageNumber="266" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B23FE171FFB06652C6A5E43633D1FCF9" blockId="7.[151,794,1569,1977]" lastBlockId="7.[831,1474,730,881]" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C6A5E4363668F9B1" bold="true" box="[151,269,1570,1593]" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB06652C726E435355AF9B1" box="[276,575,1569,1593]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brevirostratus">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C726E435355AF9B1" box="[276,575,1569,1593]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">Cnesterodon brevirostratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is diagnosed by the following autapomorphies: (1) snout blunt; (2) presence of small scales covering lateral and ventral region of body below pectoral fin in adult females; (3) bony style of ray 3 of gonopodium of fully developed mature males large and sinuous, covered with few membranous tissue (Rosa &amp; Costa, 1993; fig. 11). Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB06652C78EE4F6350BF971" box="[444,622,1761,1785]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brevirostratus">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C78EE4F6350BF971" box="[444,622,1761,1785]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">C. brevirostratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is readily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB06652C71CE51636B0F891" authorityName="Lucinda &amp; Garavello" authorityYear="2001" box="[302,469,1794,1817]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="omorgmatos">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C71CE5163625F891" box="[302,320,1794,1817]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C77CE51636B0F891" box="[334,469,1794,1817]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">omorgmatos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB06652C439E5163516F891" authorityName="Meyer &amp; Etzel" authorityYear="2001" box="[523,627,1793,1817]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="raddai">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C439E5163578F891" box="[523,541,1794,1817]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C419E5153516F891" box="[555,627,1793,1817]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">raddai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by dark brown blotches along body sides (forming bars 
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C40CE5363531F8B1" box="[574,596,1826,1849]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">vs</emphasis>
. circular or irregular, respectively). 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB06652C763E5553514F8D1" box="[337,625,1857,1881]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brevirostratus">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C763E5553514F8D1" box="[337,625,1857,1881]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">Cnesterodon brevirostratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB06652C6E0E576363DF8F1" authorityName=", Haseman" authorityYear="1911" box="[210,344,1890,1913]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="carnegiei">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C6E0E5763781F8F1" box="[210,228,1890,1913]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C6C0E576363DF8F1" box="[242,344,1890,1913]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">carnegiei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB06652C754E576369EF8F1" authorityName="Lucinda &amp; Garavello" authorityYear="2001" box="[358,507,1889,1913]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hypselurus">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C754E576361DF8F1" box="[358,376,1890,1913]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C7B4E575369EF8F1" box="[390,507,1889,1913]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">hypselurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB06652C405E5763592F8F1" box="[567,759,1889,1913]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="septentrionalis">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C405E576352CF8F1" box="[567,585,1890,1913]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C464E5753592F8F1" box="[598,759,1889,1913]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">septentrionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by dark bars on sides of body, mostly confined to midline, covering less than three scales in a transverse row, never extending to dorsal and ventral profiles (
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C29EE0CE33A7FD79" box="[1196,1218,730,753]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">vs</emphasis>
. dark bars of body very elongate reaching dorsal and ventral profiles, covering more than four scales in a transverse row). The absence of a longitudinal dark brown band along flank differentiates 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB06652C39AE12E34BDFCF9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brevirostratus">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C39AE12E32DFFCD9" box="[1448,1466,826,849]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C50DE14D34BDFCF9" box="[831,984,857,881]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">brevirostratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB06652C22BE14E33C9FCF9" authorityName="Lucinda &amp; Garavello" authorityYear="2001" box="[1049,1196,857,881]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hypselurus">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C22BE14E334EFCF9" box="[1049,1067,858,881]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C205E14D33C9FCF9" box="[1079,1196,857,881]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">hypselurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FA9AB2FAFFB06652C50DE18E34BDFBB9" pageId="7" pageNumber="266" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B23FE171FFB06652C50DE18E34BDFBB9" blockId="7.[831,1474,921,1073]" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C50DE18E34B6FC39" bold="true" box="[831,979,922,945]" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB06652C5EFE18D326CFC39" box="[989,1289,921,945]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brevirostratus">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C5EFE18D326CFC39" box="[989,1289,921,945]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">Cnesterodon brevirostratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits the upper portion of the rio Pelotas and rio Canoas of the rio 
<collectingCountry id="CA97A1E1FFB06652C3BDE1AE3417FC79" name="Uruguay" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
drainage, the rio Jacuí, the headwaters of the rio Maquiné in the Tramandaí system, and the headwaters of rio Itajaí 
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C38BE1EE32A7FB99" box="[1465,1474,1018,1041]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">-</emphasis>
Açu drainage.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FA9AB2FAFFB06652C50DE64E3481FB59" pageId="7" pageNumber="266" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B23FE171FFB06652C50DE64E3481FB59" blockId="7.[831,1474,1113,1233]" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C50DE64E34CBFBF9" bold="true" box="[831,942,1114,1137]" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">Remarks.</emphasis>
The color pattern of 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB06652C2B4E64E325FFBF9" box="[1158,1338,1113,1137]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brevirostratus">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C2B4E64E33FDFBF9" box="[1158,1176,1114,1137]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C291E64D325FFBF9" box="[1187,1338,1113,1137]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">brevirostratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quite variable. It can be a typical 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB06652C262E66D33BFFB19" box="[1104,1242,1145,1169]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="266" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB06652C262E66D33BFFB19" box="[1104,1242,1145,1169]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="266">Cnesterodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
pattern with vertical bars along flanks, a pattern of bars irregularly set and shaped, or even dotted.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
